Ad (i): The strategy for spectral resolution enhancement is similar in EPR and NMR: With increasing external Zeeman field the field-dependent spin interactions in the spin Hamiltonian are separated from the field-independent ones (see Fig. 2). In high-field EPR, the g-factor resolution is increased in relation to the hyperfine couplings, in high-field NMR the chemical-shift resolution is increased in relation to the spin–spin couplings.Fig. 2
