				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$I=1/2$$\end{document} with hyperfine interaction), Fig. 16 depicts the different forms of pulse-driven polarization transfer in Davies ENDOR (Fig. 16a) and EDNMR (Fig. 16b).Fig. 16
Comparison of pulsed Davies-type ENDOR a with pulsed ELDOR-detected NMR, EDNMR b phenomenological description of spin populations after the respective pulses have flipped the spin projections of the electron and nucleus for the case S=1/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
