The effect of bRC coating in a trehalose glass matrix has been thoroughly studied previously using laser-flash optical and EPR spectroscopies [8, 225, 230, 233, 252]. In bRCs, the coating with trehalose affects the electron-transfer step between the primary and secondary quinone acceptors [233] which is a conformationally gated process [253]. The trehalose matrix also influences the lifetime of the charge-separated radical-pair state, P865·+QA·-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
