				\begin{document}$$Q_{A}^{ \cdot - }$$\end{document}. To trace the exchange of water between the sugar matrix and the interior of the protein, the use of isotope-labeled water is essential, with regard to both deuterium and oxygen-17. By high-field EPR, we can test how the hydration of the sugar matrix translates into water exchange between the sugar matrix and either protein surface or protein interior.

