For ENDOR experiments, the cw variant of the probehead had to be modified [303]. The standard cw cavity is replaced by a gold-plated bronze TE011 cavity, the body of which is slotted with regular slots of 0.3 mm width and 0.6 mm separation to reduce rf-induced eddy currents. The slots slightly reduce QU\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
