Several probeheads have been developed for EPR and ENDOR measurements at 360 GHz [152, 313]. The ENDOR version is shown in Fig. 25. Both EPR and ENDOR probeheads are based on the plane-concave Fabry–Perot resonator operated in the TEM006 mode. With a resonant mirror distance d\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
